.th REWIND I 17-September-79
.sh NAME
rewind \*- rewind magtape
.sh SYNOPSIS
.bd rewind
[
.bd special
] [
.bd N
] [ \*- ]
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Rewind
rewinds magtape back to the beginning of tape.
.it Rewind
tries to rewind using both the old and new tape drivers.
.s3
Alternative names for
.it rewind
such as
.it rewind4
provide a different default tape device
according to the last digit of the name.
.s3
The options specify a non-default backup devices:
.s3
.lp +8 8
special	rewinds the given special file instead of
default ``/dev/rw_rmt0'' and then ``/dev/rmt0''.
.lp +8 8
N	backs up magtape raw device ``/dev/rw_rmtN''
where the one digit octal number N gives the unit number (default 0).
.lp +8 8
\*-	backs up magtape raw device ``/dev/rw_rmt4''.
.i0
.s3
.fi
.sh DIAGNOSTICS
Complains if the tape drive is offline or already occupied.
I/O errors from the previous close are ignored.
.sh FILES
/dev/rw_rmt?
